// Every module in this repository, wired together for local development.
//
// The satellites (integrations/*, parsers/*) each `require` a published
// version of the core. Without this workspace they would compile against that
// published version even here, so a breaking change to analyzer/ or
// middleware/ would pass CI while silently breaking every adapter. The
// workspace overrides that requirement with the working tree.
//
// No module in this repo carries a `replace` directive; this file is the only
// place local resolution is configured. It is committed so CI uses it too, and
// it is ignored entirely when someone depends on any of these modules.
//
// Releasing bumps each satellite's `require` to the new core tag (see
// CONTRIBUTING.md). That stays on main safely, precisely because the workspace
// still points local builds at the working tree.
//
// To reproduce a consumer's build instead, set GOWORK=off.

go 1.26

use (
	.
	./integrations/bunguard
	./integrations/entguard
	./integrations/gormguard
	./integrations/pgxguard
	./integrations/sqlxguard
	./integrations/xormguard
	./parsers/mysqlparser
	./parsers/pgparser
	./test/integration
)
